Will only work when I am at home on wifi.  Had to make two accounts, one with a direct LAN IP that works fine when I'm at home.  Another account for when I am away from home and not on wifi that points directly to my home IP used to work but one day just didn't anymore.  I didn't mind having to use two different accounts but now I no longer have control when I am not at home.  Yes I have my ports open and my router is configured properly.  I even put my Omni address in my DMZ and it still won't work.  I used to be a dealer and set these systems up for people.  I always had to make two accounts for them as well.  Recently one client contacted me saying they can no longer connect when they are not at home.  I went to their house and deleted and remade the accounts and it would not connect when not on wifi.  I got home and tried to connect to their home IP with the app on my phone and it worked right away!  But would not work on their phones???  And I still can't connect to my system via the internet but I can to theirs.  What is going on? It makes no sense.  It used to work just fine and nothing has changed with our routers or IP addresses.  This is so frustrating!!!!

Decided on this app instead of Superlink due to the publishing schedule of updates. This app was half the price and is still seeing updates. I run all Leviton controls (OmniPro, OmniStat, etc). App controls everything I need it to without lag when connected. A correct firewall NAT configuration will make switching between WiFi and mobile a non-issue. The vacation mode bug is still present, setting vacation mode sets the system to away. Controlling my temp, lights (via UPB), and setting security is seamless once connected. You can also see current status of all these settings as well. Obviously your data connection will affect how quick that process is. Wishlist - periodic automatic controller sync & push notifications. Each time you add buttons, flags, etc you have to re-sync. Be nice to see this happen automatically. Push notifications would be an added layer of alerts if an alarm is tripped, otherwise you'll have to rely on other methods. All in all, the app is an excellent addition to the system.

More questions/suggestions: Why do flags look like light bulbs?  Usually flags are timers or are on our off, and aren't manually set. Shouldn't they have their own tab?
replyContent: If you have a shortcut from the old version on your homepage, you'll need to delete it and add the shortcut again from the apps list to replace the icon. It seems that Android does not automatically update shortcut icons. As for the flags, they should not appear as light bulbs. We are looking into this issue and your tab suggestion. Thanks again.

content: Update 10/23/14 After YEARS, no weeks, not months, but years with an "s", we finally get an update.  I hoped for great things...What a disappointment!  To be fair, first the Pro's: 1. It's somewhat prettier 2. It doesn't crash 3.  They did warn us our account settings would be wiped out and need to be re-entered.  They were right!  That's all the Pro's I've got.  Why?  Because there is NOTHING new.  It's just some new graphics over the same app functionality.  Being redundant for emphasis, it's been YEARS!  And this is what we get?  Well, maybe they thought that the app was great as it was and satisfied the user base and there wasn't anything worthwhile adding.  Umm, nope!  I have had extensive correspondence with their management team regarding potentially great features.  Are any of them there?  Of course not.  They are actually responding to some of the comments with responses like "we will be releasing updates on a regular basis".  I am eagerly awaiting 2017!

I love that you finally updated the GUI.  Looks much nicer.   The app however is a mess.  Anytime I switch to a different app and go back to snaplink.  Snaplink locks up the second I try to control something with it.   This needs to be fixed asap.   I must first task kill snaplink then connect to the panel

Having someone answer your emails is just common courtesy, especially when you buy something from them. 10/21/14 finally a new version, trying it out now.
replyContent: We are sorry you had issues with the previous version of SnapLink and want you to know that we will be releasing updates on a regular basis. If you are still experiencing any problems with v2.0, please contact our customer support.

content: It's nice to finally see an update. Looks purely cosmetic. Screen with bulb icons shows icons stretched. Main menu icons and text too big. These folks need some UI education.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback and suggestions. We are sorry to hear you're having issues with the app. Our team is looking into the issues you reported and are working diligently to resolve them. We will be releasing updates on a regular basis. Please contact us if you have any other issues, comments, or suggestions.
